    "content": "* Manager of Sports - Fall Intramurals\n* VP Internal: Non-engineering students participating in (u)OEC.\n* Daniel: It is allowed to have someone that is not in engineering / represented programs participate in OEC so long they are an associate member. CEC is a different process and they would have to be opted in on a July 1st deadline. For OEC, should CS students be allowed?\n* Hayley: Don’t promote, but we should try to allow it and ask CSSA to pay their fees.\n* Daniel: In the event that they won, the team could be invalid if some of the members are not granted associate membership. We should confirm that CSSA will pay and that they have Associate Membership before uOEC actually happens.\n* Eric: The student list last year was not referenced.\n* Hayley: Easier to say no comp-sci students. Isn’t that how it’s supposed to be?\n* Daniel: Yeah, they technically shouldn't be going, It's easier to say no, rather than exploit the workaround of granting them associate membership. We just need to make sure we verify student lists before the competition and clearly state signup requirements.\n* Daniel: We need to opt multidisciplinary design into being CFES members so that they are eligible to attend CEC. We sent an email to the CFES VPFA, but missed the July 1st deadline.\n* Ashna: I'm still waiting on CFES VPFA to get back to me.\n* VP Internal: does anyone need Community Engagement Navigator posting? I created one for 101 week guides and committee, ESS officers, ESS board members, and uOEC committee members\n* None",
